  "prompt": "What does the Bible say about Muhammad?",
  "response": "The Bible does not specifically mention Muhammad by name. Muhammad is the founder of Islam and lived in the 7th century, while the texts that make up the Bible were completed centuries earlier. Some Muslims believe that certain passages in the Bible may contain indirect references or prophecies about Muhammad, but these interpretations are not universally accepted and are subject to theological debate.\n\nFor example, some Muslims cite Deuteronomy 18:18, which speaks of God raising up a prophet like Moses, and argue that this could refer to Muhammad. However, Christians traditionally interpret this passage as referring to Jesus Christ.\n\nOverall, the Bible itself does not explicitly mention Muhammad.",
